                <h1>How to Easily Blur Backgrounds in Photoshop</h1>
                <p>To blur the background in Photoshop, first, open your image and select the subject using the Quick Selection Tool or the Pen Tool. After isolating the subject, create a mask. Then, apply the Gaussian Blur filter to the background layer. Adjust the blur level to achieve the desired effect. Finally, save your work.</p>
